Like dreams, psychosis opens the floodgates to a flood of ideas and fantasies that come from the deeper layers of consciousness.
The perception of reality in psychosis is focused on the subject, according to Professor Thomas Fuchs, head of the psychiatry department at the Heidelberg CHU (Allgemeine Psychiatrie im Universitätsklinikum).
