How much should you be paid based on your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can find out what they would earn based on their profile, thanks to a new app from Trovit, the search engine with the largest number of short listings for real estate, jobs and vehicles in Spain.
The tool  How much should you be paid?  calculates user salaries from more than 140 000 job postings available from Trovit in Spain, using a form available on Facebook, where you have to enter your profession, years of experience, age and the city where you want to work.
In the week since the app was launched, the search engine has detected that, as a rule, the Spanish worker feels underpaid, said Trovit product manager Albert Ribera in a statement.
According to the data available to Trovità from its search engines in the UK and France, Spaniards are the least well paid.
A British computer programmer receives 45 226 euros gross per year and a French one 31 059, while a Spanish one receives 24 000 euros.
Similarly, a driver in England earns a gross annual salary of EUR 34 247, in France EUR 25 751 and in Spain EUR 16 420.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid job in Spain is as a waiter, with 11 592 net euros per year, followed by salesman, with 14 725 euros, and as a worker, with 15 667 euros.
The most searched jobs on the Internet in the last three months are driver, part-time jobs and social worker.
